wikipedia_page.main: George Fenner (born 10 February 1799 in Cambridge; died 1871 in Cambridge) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge Town Club who was active in the 1820s. He is recorded in one match in 1821, totalling 35 runs with a highest score of 34.
